CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. 26, reads:  "Unbeaten Eleven - Above is the all-victorious football squad of the Homewood Orioles.  The team is unbeaten in six games and is leading the City-County League.  Left to right, front row: E. Goodson, A. Lawson, Dunn, K. Lane, E. Simmins, G. Jackson, A. Dickerson and G. Griffen.  Second row: M. Anderson, R. Harris, L. Williamson, J. Williams, B. Weathers, R. Warrick, J. Debowe and Mason.  Back row: Andy Goodson, defensive coach; Raines, Stamp, Stewart, Watson, Parrish, Azeane, Higginbottom, Fulton and Jim Johnson, offensive coach. - Harris Photo."
